			<div style="text-align:justify;">
				<P>
					<B>Introduction</B>: Given the high competitiveness of companies nowadays, the differentiation in the performance of these is critical to their sustainability and growth. In this sense, to create and keep customers, innovation is the only way for survival.
However, to innovate requires several internal and external conditions. These features correspond to inovativdade companies, namely their propensity to innovate, generate new ideas that can be applied in new ways to approach the market, new techniques to manage their business and especially, developing new products.					<B>Objectives</B>: The main objective of this research was to determine whether the management of information and experience can contribute and drive the development of new products, and contributes, what is the degree of contribution to this development					<B>Methods</B>: The project was characterized as an exploratory, qualitative research, and the strategy used was the single case study.					<B>Results</B>: 					<B>Conclusion</B>: It was concluded that, before acting on the market the company should know him well, and especially observe the feasibility of operation. But one main driver for this market entry would be the experience of its employees and managers, and the clarity of goal, of course that goals may change over the course of the company in the market, but the main objectives should be clear at all company levels, and all employees and managers should be efficient about it. Drucker (1954) stated that the sole purpose for the existence of a company is to create a customer, and the company must meet the needs of this customer, with this, the clearer the purpose of business at all levels of the company, better understanding the employees and managers will, and as quoted by the Manager of one company that was the case study, "a client who may not have a direct relationship with the company, but it can help to have multiple projects" it is the relationships within and outside the company. Information is always key to the company´s growth, but know transform this information into knowledge is a differential for this growth.				</P>
